cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with the generalization of convolutional neural networks to Riemannian homogeneous manifolds, with a focus on applications to neuroimaging. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves theoretical contributions related to linear group equivariance systems, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The use of deep networks for classification of diffusion magnetic resonance image (dMRI) scans suggests a possible fit with the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the proof of concept experiment involving synthetic data generated on the manifold of symmetric positive definite matrices could relate to the cs.IT (Information Theory) category, which deals with mathematical foundations of data processing.
